snippet: A Census Bureau survey also found that Hispanics and Asians continue to turn out at much lower rates than other groups, and that women turn out at higher rates than men.
abstract: Census Bureau report shows that, for first time on record, turnout rate for black voters surpassed rate for whites in 2012, as more black voters went to polls than in 2008 and fewer whites did.
lead_paragraph: A Census Bureau survey also found that Hispanics and Asians continue to turn out at much lower rates than other groups, and that women turn out at higher rates than men.

headline.main: For First Time on Record, Black Voting Rate Outpaced Rate for Whites in 2012
headline.print_headline: For First Time on Record, Black Voting Rate Outpaced Rate for Whites in 2012
